server:unified callBackendTool: serverID=safeoutputs, toolName=create_pull_request, args=map[body:## Summary
- ported the `musyoku.tokyo` LDRFullFeed rule into `resources/fullfeed/plus.json`
- switched the rule to a CSS selector using the stable article body ID `#the-content`
- removed the migrated source rule from `resources/fullfeed/items_all.json`
- recorded the migration in `.github/port.md`
- updated cache memory progress in `port-progress.json`

## Why
The top page at `http://musyoku.tokyo/` is still reachable, and live article pages keep the article body in `#the-content`, so this site can be migrated from the legacy XPath-based rule to a package-native selector rule.

## Testing
- `vendor/bin/testbench fullfeed:sort`
- `composer run lint`
- `composer run test` branch:port-musyoku-tokyo-20260421 draft:true integrity:high repo:invokable/laravel-fullfeed secrecy:public title:port musyoku.tokyo rule] +2.8m
